voca — Local-first vocabulary tracker
=====================================

This plugin bundles derivative wordlist data from the following sources, all
licensed under terms compatible with the plugin's CC BY-SA 4.0 license:

1. hermitdave / FrequencyWords (OpenSubtitles 2018 word frequencies)
   - URL:     https://github.com/hermitdave/FrequencyWords
   - License: CC BY-SA 4.0
   - Used in: en/ja/ko probes (base layer)

2. Wikipedia article titles (Korean, English)
   - URL:     https://dumps.wikimedia.org/
   - License: CC BY-SA 4.0
   - Used in: ko.rare.tsv, en.rare.tsv (specialized vocabulary)

3. NINJAL Balanced Corpus of Contemporary Written Japanese (BCCWJ)
   - Short Unit Word frequency list
   - URL:     https://clrd.ninjal.ac.jp/bccwj/
   - License: redistribution permitted under NINJAL terms (see NINJAL docs)
   - Used in: ja.rare.tsv

CEFR vocabulary thresholds reference Council of Europe / Milton (2009).
Native percentile bands reference:
  - Korean: 김광해 (2003) "한국어 어휘 빈도조사" / 국립국어원
  - Japanese: NTT 語彙数推定テスト 補正版
  - English: testyourvocab.com (2013, 2M+ samples)

Each upstream source retains its own license; modifications and derivations
in this repository are released under CC BY-SA 4.0 to maintain compatibility.
